snippet.textDisplay: I hope y’all don’t purchase Pella Series 350 “Superior” windows. Before Hurricane Harvey, we completed three rooms. Contractors replaced our living room, dining, and kitchen windows, and patio sliding glass door with Pella’s “best”. Ha! All are hurricane rated, but the picture window in the kitchen and the patio door failed, miserably. It took use 18 months to get Pella out to make an assessment on the window and door, and then charged me tho replace them, because they were over a year old, even though I had requested a technician 6 months after installation. Needless to say, Pella didn’t replace any more windows for us. I contacted Window World, got the rest of my homes windows replaced with windows that are equal to or better than Pella’s top of the line windows. I would hate to see them take advantage of you or anyone else. You’re doing a great job with your rebuild, and I enjoy seeing your progress. God Bless.
